race.description: Racing Nation On Power Fm Maiden Plate
race.comment: ATTACK FORCE (1) wound up strongly last time out to finish a long neck over 1200m at Kilcoy. Raced a $3.7F in that and hits this at peak fitness. Will wind up late and be tough to hold out. HIDEYOSHI (2) resumes for the sharp Currie yard and has shown enough to suggest she can feature. The extra gear comes off and the blinkers go on for the first time. The betting will be key. Ditto with STRAIGHT BLAST (8), who draws awkwardly, but his recent trials suggest he's going to resume as a much-improved galloper. Has to be kept safe. HABERFIELD (9) came from back and wasn't beaten far here three weeks ago, improving. Maps well and is still shy of her NSW peaks. Cartwright is reunited, and she'd be in the mix if near best.
